{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a75e23c5-44e5-45ca-85e6-e4fc896ae4b9","content":"To switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0:\n\n1. **Remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Remove this line entirely -->\n   <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   ```\n\n2. **That's it.** MSTest.Sdk defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform when `UseVSTest` is not set (or is `false`).\n\n**Key differences to be aware of:**\n- Run tests with `dotnet test` as usual (SDK ≥ 3.8 supports it).\n- CLI output format changes slightly.\n- Some VSTest-specific `.runsettings` options may not apply; check for warnings.\n- If you use `dotnet test --filter`, the filter syntax is the same.\n\n**Optional but recommended:** add an `<EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>` property if you want to be explicit, though the SDK sets this by default.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d96de173-77e8-4a96-8ef3-54cf62675730","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in their MSTest project. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing configuration. Let me check if there's relevant documentation in the repository first.","outputTokens":306,"requestId":"CFC5:180DF7:5F728E1:6AABD19:69EC0EC7"},"id":"3d161657-2595-4a64-afda-8e3d6fe7b3af","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:46:06.745Z","parentId":"8be3eb9c-0351-4b80-b7be-4b8f8e1f7e12"}
